<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 08 at 12:11AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...PATCHY FREEZING DRIZZLE REMAINS POSSIBLE TONIGHT...
Patchy freezing drizzle mixed with snow flakes will continue
to be possible in some parts of the region through the rest of the
night in the southwest Adirondacks, Mohawk Valley, Schoharie
Valley, Saratoga Region, the Capital District into the central
Taconics and the Berkshires. Where freezing drizzle falls, any
untreated sfc will likely turn icy given temperatures remaining in
the 20s overnight. Use caution if traveling the rest of tonight.</description>
